text: Jean Dumont (27 November 1930 – 18 January 2021) was a French politician. He was born in Thouars, France. Dumont was a member of the Republican Party. From 1986 to 1995, Dumont was a member of the Senate. Dumont died in Parthenay, France on 18 January 2021, aged 90. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Politicians from Nouvelle-Aquitaine Category:People from Deux-Sèvres
